sources.description:
Out of the shadows of a vice-ridden city comes James M. Cain's most explosive drama!
An urban wheeler-dealer gets involved in organized crime, corrupt city politics and graft while falling in love with the fiancée of the newly elected mayor.

Original title: Slightly Scarlet (1956)

Director: Allan Dwan
Writers: Robert Blees, James M. Cain
Stars: John Payne, Rhonda Fleming, Arlene Dahl
Genres: Crime, Drama, Film-Noir
